1. GitLab runner recovery and queue reduction

Problem: GitLab runners go offline, fill disks, lose registration, hang jobs, or become overloaded. Developers wait on pipelines instead of delivering code.

Telemetry: GitLab runner status, Prometheus queue/utilization metrics, Nagios host/service checks, Splunk runner logs.

AAP remediation: Restart runner service, clean approved workspace/cache paths, validate registration, drain unhealthy runners, re-enable healthy runners, provision standby runners where supported.

Savings: Less pipeline downtime, less engineer babysitting, faster build/test cycles.

