2. Artifact repository and container registry reliability

Problem: Builds fail when artifact repositories, package mirrors, or container registries become unavailable, slow, full, or out of sync.

Telemetry: Prometheus latency/storage metrics, Nagios availability checks, Splunk service logs, registry/repository health APIs.

AAP remediation: Restart known services, validate mounts/storage, clear safe temp areas, trigger mirror sync, fail over to approved secondary endpoints, verify artifact pull/push after recovery.

Savings: Prevents software factory stoppages caused by broken dependencies.

⸻

3. Restricted-network content mirror health

Problem: DSO teams in restricted or disconnected networks lose time when approved software, packages, containers, or automation content are stale, missing, or inconsistently mirrored.

Telemetry: Mirror freshness checks, repository metadata checks, registry sync status, Splunk logs, Prometheus/Nagios availability.

AAP remediation: Trigger approved sync jobs, validate metadata, compare source/target manifests, repair failed syncs, generate mirror status evidence.

Savings: Reduces manual mirror troubleshooting and keeps disconnected software delivery moving.

