Problem: Integration labs and test environments drift, get left in bad states, or require manual reset before test events.

Telemetry: Host/service checks, lab reservation state, test harness status, VM/container health, Splunk logs.

AAP remediation: Reset systems to a known-good baseline, restart simulators/services, restore VM snapshots, validate required ports/services, release stuck reservations, produce readiness status.

Savings: Less waiting for labs, fewer delayed test windows, faster integration cycles.

