7. Enterprise recurring-issue detection and Jira problem creation

Problem: Teams often fix the same failure repeatedly without the data needed to justify a permanent fix.

Telemetry: Splunk saved searches, Prometheus alert history, GitLab job failures, Nagios state changes, AAP job results.

AAP / event action: Normalize events into an issue fingerprint such as runner_pool + failure_type + service + environment, count occurrences, suppress noise, and create or update Jira only when the pattern crosses a threshold.

Ticket logic: Example: “Create Jira if this failure happens 5 times in 24 hours, impacts 3 or more teams, or consumes more than X minutes of pipeline downtime.” Jira supports issue creation through REST APIs, so this could be integrated as part of the workflow.  

Why it saves money: Turns noisy recurring failures into actionable engineering backlog instead of endless one-off troubleshooting.

