Problem: Developers waste time figuring out whether a pipeline failed because of their code or because the software factory infrastructure broke.

Telemetry: GitLab job logs, runner health, artifact repository status, Kubernetes deployment events, Splunk error patterns.

AAP action: Collect evidence, classify common failure signatures, retry known transient platform failures, route likely code failures back to the developer, and create Jira for recurring platform issues.

Ticket logic: Jira ticket only when failures are infrastructure-patterned and repeated, not for every failed pipeline.

Why it saves money: Reduces unnecessary developer interruptions and DSO support tickets.

