AAP action: Add temporary runners, scale approved worker pools, power on standby resources, drain unhealthy nodes, and scale down after demand drops.

Ticket logic: Create Jira capacity tickets when scaling actions repeat frequently or demand consistently exceeds baseline.

Why it saves money: Improves throughput without permanently overprovisioning.

