Phase 3 — Update your rootless runner config

Open:

vi ~/.config/gitlab-runner/config.toml

Find your [runners.docker] section and add a volume for the fixture root.

Example using a real absolute path:

volumes = [
  "/cache",
  "/run/user/2271030/podman/podman.sock:/run/docker.sock",
  "/run/user/2271030/podman/podman.sock:/var/run/docker.sock",
  "/home/YOUR_USER/.local/share/aerolit-molecule:/home/YOUR_USER/.local/share/aerolit-molecule:ro"
]

Keep your existing socket volumes. Just add the fixture mount.

Also add this near the [[runners]] level if you do not already have an environment entry:

environment = [
  "AEROLIT_FIXTURE_ROOT=/home/YOUR_USER/.local/share/aerolit-molecule"
]

If you already have an environment = [...] list, append the new value instead of creating a second one.

Then restart your rootless runner:

systemctl --user daemon-reload
systemctl --user restart gitlab-runner
systemctl --user status gitlab-runner --no-pager

The important detail: the fixture path should be mounted into the job container at the same absolute path that exists on the runner host.

That matters because Molecule creates sibling UBI containers through the Podman socket. So this path:

/home/YOUR_USER/.local/share/aerolit-molecule

needs to be valid from the host Podman point of view and visible inside the CI job container.

