Phase 6 — Fix role dependency resolution

Your current setup symlinks the role under test into the temporary Molecule scenario. Keep that.

Add the hub as fallback.

Because your role projects may be nested like this:

roles/administration/root-password-management
roles/common/repo-client

you should not assume all roles live directly under one flat roles/ directory. Build the hub role path dynamically.

Add this helper in the compliance-center script:

build_hub_roles_path() {
  local hub_roles_dir="$1"
  if [ ! -d "$hub_roles_dir" ]; then
    return 0
  fi
  find "$hub_roles_dir" \
    -type f \
    -path '*/tasks/main.yml' \
    -print \
  | while read -r main_yml; do
      role_dir="$(dirname "$(dirname "$main_yml")")"
      dirname "$role_dir"
    done \
  | sort -u \
  | paste -sd ':' -
}

Then when you create the scenario:

HUB_ROLES_PATH="$(build_hub_roles_path "$AEROLIT_COLLECTION_HUB/roles")"
export ANSIBLE_ROLES_PATH="$SCEN_DIR/roles"
if [ -n "$HUB_ROLES_PATH" ]; then
  export ANSIBLE_ROLES_PATH="$ANSIBLE_ROLES_PATH:$HUB_ROLES_PATH"
fi
export ANSIBLE_ROLES_PATH="$ANSIBLE_ROLES_PATH:/usr/share/ansible/roles"
export ANSIBLE_COLLECTIONS_PATH="$AEROLIT_COLLECTION_HUB/collections:/usr/share/ansible/collections"

Then print it:

echo "=== AeroLIT Molecule dependency resolution ==="
echo "Role under test: $ROLE_NAME"
echo "Scenario dir: $SCEN_DIR"
echo "Hub: $AEROLIT_COLLECTION_HUB"
echo "ANSIBLE_ROLES_PATH=$ANSIBLE_ROLES_PATH"
echo "ANSIBLE_COLLECTIONS_PATH=$ANSIBLE_COLLECTIONS_PATH"

This gives you the behavior you want:

role under test
  -> current branch from the GitLab checkout
dependency roles
  -> pinned hub snapshot
system fallback
